casebody.data:
Gerald A. GRACE, Relator,
v.
SMITH FOUNDRY COMPANY and TRIFAC Workers' Compensation Fund, with Claims Administered by Meadowbrook Claims Services, Respondents,
and
Warehousemen, Drivers & Helpful Benefit Association, HealthPartners, Inc., Noran Neurological Clinic, and Abbott Northwestern Hospital, Intervenors. A18-1591 Supreme Court of Minnesota. February 12, 2019 James T. Hansing, James T. Hansing Law Office, Minneapolis, Minnesota, for relator. Arlen R. Logren and Beth A. Butler, Peterson, Logren & Kilbury, P.A., Roseville, Minnesota, for respondents. Considered and decided by the court without oral argument.

ORDER

Based upon all the files, records and proceedings herein,

IT IS HEREBY ORDERED that the decision of the Workers' Compensation Court of Appeals filed August 30, 2018, be, and the same is, affirmed without opinion. See Hoff v. Kempton, 317 N.W.2d 361 , 366 (Minn. 1982) (summary dispositions "have no precedential value because they do not commit the court to any particular point of view," doing no more than establishing the law of the case).

BY THE COURT:

/s/ ______________________________

Anne K. McKeig

Associate Justice
